A new Sector Commander of the Kwara State Command of the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) has been deployed to the state. Corp Commander Fredrick Ade Ogidan who has since assumed duty, succeeds Jonathan Owoade who is on transfer to Zone 6 Port Hacourt following his recent promotion. According to a statement issued on Wednesday by the Chief Route Commander, Dapo James, until his new appointment, Corp Ogidan was the Kaduna State sector head of operations. The statement added that Ogidan will embark on â€œfamiliarisation visit to sister agencies and stakeholders following the completion of the Sallah special patrol operations.